  "body": "**Steps to Reproduce**\r\nIn order to replicate the behavior, please provide a detailed list of steps:\r\n1. Start Nethermind on for example Gnosis chain with FullSync setting (archive config + Hybrid Pruning)\r\n2. Wait for all blocks to be Downloaded BUT not Processed yet\r\n3. When all downloaded wait until disk space will start running out (I had machine with 320 GB but machine with 200GB would be also good)\r\n4. When first info about space running out are appearing, restart node\r\n5. After restart, node should be in \"partially offline\" mode, meaning that it is syncing already downloaded blocks.\r\n6. Observe logs\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior**\r\nNo free space checks are visible.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nEven in partial offline mode those logs should be visible - seems like nethermind is not yet fully initialized and plugin responsible for check is not loaded yet. I have a machine which already have 0% free space and no logs still.",
